item.title: CVE-2022-2647|2024-08-03T00:46:03.488Z -- unspecified -- jeecg-boot
item.description: A vulnerability was found in jeecg-boot. It has been declared as critical. This vulnerability affects unknown code of the file /api/. The manipulation of the argument file leads to unrestricted upload. The attack can be initiated remotely. The exploit has been disclosed to the public and may be used. VDB-205594 is the identifier assigned to this vulnerability.
